Then \(p\times q=(2a-b)\times (4a-5b)=-6(a\times b)\) \[=-6|a||b|\sin \cfrac{\pi }{4} \hat{n}=-6\times \cfrac{1}{\sqrt{2} } \hat{n}=-3\sqrt{2} \, \hat{n}.\]

Hence the area of the given parallelogram \[=\cfrac{1}{2} |p\times q|\, =\cfrac{3}{\sqrt{2} } .\]

quest_title: The temperature of source increased by 100k then efficiency of carnot engine increases from 30% to 40%. The temperature of sink is
explanation_txt:
\(\begin{array}{l}{\eta_{1}=\left(1-\cfrac{T_{2}}{T_{1}}\right) \times 100 \%} \\ {\text { or, } \cfrac{T_{2}}{T_{1}}=1-\cfrac{30}{100}=\cfrac{7}{10} \ldots \ldots \text { (i) }}\end{array}\)

Second case

\(\begin{array}{l}{\eta_{2}=\left(1-\cfrac{T_{2}}{T_{1}+100}\right) \times 100 \%} \\ {\text { or, } \cfrac{40}{100}=1-\cfrac{T_{2}}{T_{1}+100}} \\ {\text { or, } \cfrac{T_{2}}{T_{1}+100}=1-\cfrac{2}{5}=\cfrac{3}{5} \cdots(\text { ii })}\end{array}\)

Dividing (i) by (ii)

\(\begin{array}{l}{\cfrac{\mathrm{T}_{2}}{\mathrm{T}_{1}} \times \cfrac{\mathrm{T}_{1}+100}{\mathrm{T}_{2}}=\cfrac{7}{10} \times \cfrac{5}{3}} \\ {\text { or, } 6 \mathrm{T}_{1}+600=7 \mathrm{T}_{1}} \\ {\text { or, } \mathrm{T}_{1}=600 \mathrm{K}} \\ {\therefore \mathrm{T}_{2}=\cfrac{7}{10} \times 600=420 \mathrm{k}}\end{array}\)

quest_title: If \( \tan x = \cos x \) the value of \(\sin x\) is:
explanation_txt:
\( \tan x = \cos x \implies \sin x = \cos^2 x \)

So, \(\sin^2 x + \sin x - 1 = 0 \)

This gives \( \sin x = \cfrac{-1 \pm \sqrt{5}}{2} \)

As, \( |\sin x| \le 1 \), \( \cfrac {-1-\sqrt{5}}{2} \) is neglected.
